From: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>
Date: 2026-05-14
Subject: [PATCH] ps4_mts: v115 — emulate gbe:ctrl done by clearing IRQ bit12

v112 proved that simply re-arming BAR+0x204 after the bit-18 init-mode
handshake is too literal: the master IRQ block comes back, but bit18
immediately reasserts and the useful RX/TX IRQs still do not take over.

The next Orbis-derived hotswap experiment is to emulate the missing
`gbe:ctrl` completion edge.  Ghidra analysis of the Orbis ctrl path
(FUN_ffffffffc85f0190 / FUN_ffffffffc85f1e80) showed that after it
runs mts_init_rings_kick/link/RMU work, it clears BAR+0x54 bit 12
(mask &= ~0x1000).  Our Linux path never did that; v112 re-armed the
master IRQ block with bit12 still present in the saved 0x007bfffe mask.

Add MTS_IRQ_CTRL_DONE_BIT and clear it in two places:
  - immediately after the v110 BAR+0x1c8 rings-ready marker in ndo_open;
  - inside the bit18 handshake before re-arming BAR+0x204.

Expected signal: BAR+0x54 logs as 0x007beffe after the completion edge,
bit18 stops storming after the one-shot handshake, and RX/TX/link IRQ
patterns become visible instead of re-entering the init-mode loop.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/sony/ps4_mts.c | 42 ++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/sony/ps4_mts.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/sony/ps4_mts.c
@@ -138,6 +138,7 @@
  */
 #define MTS_IRQ_BIT18		0x00040000
 #define MTS_IRQ_MASK_FULL_VAL	0x007bfffe	/* v111: bit 18 included */
+#define MTS_IRQ_CTRL_DONE_BIT	0x00001000	/* v115: gbe:ctrl clears BAR+0x54 bit 12 */
 
 #define MTS_PHY_CTRL_PERIOD_MS	3000	/* gbe:phy_ctrl cadence */
 #define MTS_DBG_TIMER_PERIOD_MS	5000	/* debug telemetry dump cadence */
@@ -966,23 +967,23 @@ static irqreturn_t mts_intr(int irq, void *dev_id)
 	    (status & ~mts->saved_irq_mask) == MTS_IRQ_BIT18) {
 		mts->irq_block_armed = false;
 		writel(0, mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_ENABLE_FULL);
-		writel(mts->saved_irq_mask, mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_MASK);
+		/*
+		 * v115: emulate the gbe:ctrl completion edge found in Orbis
+		 * FUN_ffffffffc85f0190/FUN_ffffffffc85f1e80.  After ctrl does
+		 * mts_init_rings_kick/link/RMU work it clears BAR+0x54 bit 12
+		 * (mask &= ~0x1000).  v112 re-armed BAR+0x204 with bit12 still
+		 * present and immediately re-entered the bit-18 storm.  Clear
+		 * bit12 before re-arm; if this is the missing init-done ack,
+		 * bit18 should stop reasserting and useful RX/TX IRQs can surface.
+		 */
+		writel(mts->saved_irq_mask & ~MTS_IRQ_CTRL_DONE_BIT,
+		       mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_MASK);
 		(void)readl(mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_MASK);
-		/*
-		 * v112: Orbis's mts_intr re-arms BAR+0x204 = 0x10001388 at the
-		 * TOP of every ISR call (gated on softc+0x309c==0).  We don't
-		 * have a per-call first-call setup, so we re-arm inline here
-		 * after clearing.  Without this, no further MSIs are delivered:
-		 * v111 cleared BAR+0x204 = 0 and stayed there → total_irq stuck
-		 * at 1, MAC asserted RX_AVAIL in BAR+0x50 but ISR never re-entered.
-		 * The udelay(10) gives the MAC's state machine a chance to fully
-		 * transition out of init mode before we re-arm.
-		 */
 		udelay(10);
 		writel(MTS_IRQ_ENABLE_FULL_VAL, mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_ENABLE_FULL);
 		(void)readl(mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_ENABLE_FULL);
 		dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
-			 "v112: bit-18 handshake completed — re-armed BAR+0x204=0x%08x BAR+0x54=0x%08x\n",
+			 "v115: bit18 + gbe:ctrl-done handshake — BAR+0x204=0x%08x BAR+0x54=0x%08x\n",
 			 readl(mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_ENABLE_FULL),
 			 readl(mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_MASK));
 		return IRQ_HANDLED;
@@ -1517,10 +1518,25 @@ static int mts_open(struct net_device *ndev)
 	 */
 	{
 		u32 v1c8_before = readl(mts->bar + MTS_MCAST_MASK);
+		u32 mask_before, mask_after;
+
 		writel((v1c8_before & ~0x440u) | 0x40u, mts->bar + MTS_MCAST_MASK);
 		dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
 			 "v110: BAR+0x1c8 0x%08x -> 0x%08x (rings-ready marker per Orbis)\n",
 			 v1c8_before, readl(mts->bar + MTS_MCAST_MASK));
+
+		/*
+		 * v115: gbe:ctrl completion emulation.  Orbis ctrl path clears
+		 * BAR+0x54 bit12 after mts_init_rings_kick / link/RMU handling.
+		 * Do it immediately after our ring-kick marker too, so the MAC
+		 * sees the completion edge even before the first bit18 IRQ race.
+		 */
+		mask_before = readl(mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_MASK);
+		mask_after = mask_before & ~MTS_IRQ_CTRL_DONE_BIT;
+		writel(mask_after, mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_MASK);
+		dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+			 "v115: gbe:ctrl-done BAR+0x54 0x%08x -> 0x%08x (clear bit12)\n",
+			 mask_before, readl(mts->bar + MTS_IRQ_MASK));
 	}
 
 	/* 4. Wait for MAC bit 0 latch.  v91 took ~5s from engine start
